    • Method Detail

      • parseItem

        CBORItem parseItem(String input)
            throws CBORDiagnosticNotationException
        Parse the given string as the CBOR Diagnostic Notation and generates a corresponding CBORItem instance.

        For example, when "h'0102'" is given, an instance of CBORByteArray should be returned. Likewise, when "0(\"2013-03-21T20:04:00Z\")" is given, a CBORTaggedItem instance that wraps a CBORString instance should be returned.

        Parameters:
        input - A string representing a CBOR item in the CBOR Diagnostic Notation.
        Returns:
        A CBORItem instance represented by the given string.
        Throws:
        CBORDiagnosticNotationException - The given string does not conform to the CBOR Diagnostic Notation, or the parser implementation does not support the notation used in the given string.
